Installation
Clone the repository and run npm install to install the necessary dependencies.

command : npm install

Packages Used
axios: ^1.6.7
cors: ^2.8.5
express: ^4.18.2
mysql: ^2.18.1
mysql2: ^3.9.1


Development Tools Used
nodemon

Database
AWS RDS (MySQL): Used to seed the data from the API.  (for Production)
MySQL Workbench (Local Server) for testing.

File Structure
database.js: Database configuration.
controllers/: Folder containing logic (controller functions).
routes/products.js: Route handling for /product endpoints.


Endpoints
All endpoints are accessed through port 9090.

Initialize Database
Endpoint: GET /product/initializeDB
Description: Initializes the database.
Controller Function: initializeDB in initializeDB.js
Example: https://localhost:9090/product/initializeDB

Get All Transactions
Endpoint: GET /product/alltransactions
Description: Retrieves all transactions.
Controller Function: getalltransactions in getalltransactions.js
Query Parameters: month, page, search, perPage


Get Statistics
Endpoint: GET /product/statistics
Description: Retrieves statistics.
Controller Function: getStatistics in getStatistics.js
Query Parameters: month


Get Bar Chart
Endpoint: GET /product/barchart
Description: Retrieves a bar chart.
Controller Function: getbarchart in getbarchart.js
Query Parameters: month


Get Pie Chart
Endpoint: GET /product/piechart
Description: Retrieves a pie chart.
Controller Function: getpiechart in getpiechart.js
Query Parameters: month


Get Combined Data
Endpoint: GET /product/combined-data
Description: Retrieves combined data of statistics, bar chart, and pie chart (takes month as query parameter).






